AGI - Eyes pointed to the starry sky this night, to admire the Pink Moon, which towards 01:49 of April 24 will reach its peak. Symbol of rebirth and cosmic spectacle, the Moon full of April, the fourth of 2024, will be observable for about three days. The phenomenon will reach the best visibility in the constellation of the Virgin, but it is important to consult the local times linked to the appearance of the Moon to identify the optimal position in which to observe the show.
&nbsp;
Despite the adjective, our natural satellite will not show pink nuances, but will appear with its usual white. In fact, there are many appellations with which we refer to this event, but the "pink" depends on the period in which the event takes place rather than its manifestation. In these days, the flowering of the Phlox subulata, also known as pink moss, is a plant species typical of spring, of which it is also a symbol. The "Rose Moon" also recalls the periods in which time scanning was linked to natural signals.
&nbsp;
According to the Maine Farmers' Almanac, the lunar months are associated with the traditions of the Native Americans, and April refers to the month of rebirth. Many species of fish lay eggs in April, so the Pink Moon also takes the name of "Luna dei Pesci". In the Oglala culture it is also called "Luna dell'Erba Rossa che Appare", the Tlingit refer to this phenomenon as "Luna dell'Erba che Germoglia". For the Choctaw it is the "Luna del Mirtilli", and the Cherokee instead use the locution "Luna dei Fiori", the name for the last film by Martin Scorsese, "Killers of the Flower Moon". Regardless of the denomination it takes in different cultures, the Rosa Moon represents rebirth, spring, and is a special occasion to observe the sky and enjoy the spectacle of the Universe.&nbsp;

